title: For Sale:  AR-15/M4 with upgrades
postcontent:
I have a really nice, brand new (just built by me) AR-15 in M4 configuration.
I enjoy building them, but don't have much use for it afterward, so it's up for sale here. :)
It will be sold my me as a personal transaction, no dealer involvement required, unless you need me to ship it. In that case, you'll of course have to arrange for a dealer on your end to handle the transfer for you.

The gun is a typical M4, with 16" barrel, flat top, A2 flash hider etc..

It has the following upgrades/accessories: 
(all parts are standard black unless noted otherwise)
- Magpul MOE handguard
- Magpul PTS MOE handguard sling point
- Magpul PTS MOE pistol grip in Dark Earth (not pictured)
- Magpul PTS MBUS sights in Dark Earth (not pictured) (OPTIONAL +$20)
- Custom 5 lb trigger with NO creep and very little takeup, very smooth
- Magpul PTS CTR stock, customized to be very smooth, with no rattle at any point.
- Hammer buffer to allow safe dry-firing.
- ASAP-style single point ambidextrous receiver sling point
- Low profile gas block with top rail (great for free floated handguards)
- Ambidextrous tactical charging handle latch
- Magpul PTS extended trigger guard (for gloves) (I have both Black and Dark Earth, your choice)
- FAB Defense MWG (Mag Well Foregrip), adds a nice grip point in front of the mag well
- Includes 1 new USGI magazine

Also available is a REALLY nice holographic sight.
It's a clone of the EOTech EXPS, which is one of the new versions with the controls on the side. This is handy if you plan to use it with a magnifier, as the controls stay out of the way.
The sight is brand new, includes the box and all paperwork, and comes with a ScopeCoat to protect it. It's $100 extra if purchased with the gun, or $125 by itself.
Please Note: The sight in the photos is NOT the EOTech clone, it's just a cheap one I had laying around that I stuck on there for fun.

I also have a Magpul Dynamics MS2 tactical sling that I'll let go for $15.

The gun is basically brand new. It's had about 6 rounds through it for function testing, and will have maybe 10 more to sight in the new holosight when it comes in.

More photos available in a gallery here (copy/paste into your address bar to view): https://skydrive.live.com/redir.aspx?cid=9d816cdbeb938785&resid=9D816CDBEB938785!7995&parid=9D816CDBEB938785!119&authkey=!ANHrOxjlpsGYcwQ

PLEASE NOTE: The custom target grip in the photos is no longer available and is not included with the rifle. The Magpul MOE grip (not pictured) is still included.

title: For Sale/Trade:  M48 Mauser
postcontent:
The M48 Mauser is a post World War II Yugoslavian version of the Belgian Fabrique Nationale designed Mauser Model 1924 short rifle which was produced under contract by the "Kingdom of Yugoslavia" beginning in 1928 and ending with the Nazi occupation in 1941. After World War II, the Yugoslavs took this design and incorporated modifications based upon Germany's Mauser Karabiner 98k. Although similar in general appearance to that of the German rifle, many of the parts of these two rifles are not interchangeable, especially the bolt and related action parts. The main difference between the M48 and the K98k is that the M48 uses an intermediate-length receiver. They are usually easily identified by the top handguard, which extends behind the rear sight and ends just in front of the receiver ring, although this feature exists on other models as well. 

That being said the gun shoots great. Email me with offers.
